          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The carbon targets were produced by evaporating carbon",
                "onto a glass plate, 20 to 50 mug/cm**2 thickness.",
                "A 2 mm tantalum foil was used to stop all C-11 nuclei",
                "in forward direction. In backward direction an Al foil",
                "of 220 g/cm**2 was used. The catcher foils were",
                "irradiated at different energies in order to correct",
                "the total activity induced in the target arrangement.",
                "The carbon content of the tantalum foil was about",
                "0.6 mug/cm**2, whereas the corresponding carbon",
                "concentration in aluminum amounted to 3 mug/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
